Section 5. Section 20-7-118, MCA, is amended to read:
"20-7-118. Remote instruction. (1) A school district may provide remote instruction, including the
provision of services through electronic means. A district shall comply with any rules adopted by the board of
public education that specify standards for remote instruction. The provision of remote instruction by a district is
limited to pupils:
(a) meeting the residency requirements for that district as provided in 1-1-215;
(b) living in the district and eligible for educational services under the Individuals With Disabilities
Education Act or under 29 U.S.C. 794; or
(c) enrolled in the district and physically attending a school or offsite instructional setting of the
district under an attendance agreement pursuant to Title 20, chapter 5, part 3; or
(d) seeking remote instruction in the nearest another district when the pupil's district of residence
does not provide remote or in-person instruction in an equivalent course. A course is not equivalent if the
