Section 7. Section 20-9-505, MCA, is amended to read:
"20-9-505. Purpose and establishment of nonoperating fund. (1) The trustees of a district that will
not operate a school during the ensuing school fiscal year shall establish a nonoperating fund on the first day of
the school fiscal year. In establishing the nonoperating fund, the trustees shall cause the transfer of the end-of-
the-year fund balance of each fund maintained by the district during the immediately preceding school fiscal
year to the nonoperating fund. However, fund balances of the debt service fund and the miscellaneous
programs fund, if any, must be maintained in their individual funds.
